        {
            "type":"/pattern-library/section-block",
            "anchor" : "containers",
            "data":[
                {
                    "type":"type/h3",
                    "data":"Containers"
                },
                "There are three main classes that make up a container: 'wrapper', 'section' and 'layout'.",
                "The 'wrapper' class sets the maximum page width to 72rem (1152px).",
                "The '<a href='#section'>section</a>' class controls the vertical spacing of a section.",
                "The '<a href='#layout'>layout</a>' class controls the horizontal spacing of a section.",
                "Each container can include an optional <a href='/pattern-library/themes/'>theme</a> if needed. ",
                {
                    "type":"raw",
                    "data":"<hr class='hr--bleed'/>"
                },
                {
                    "type":"type/h4",
                    "data":"Section"
                },
                "The 'section' class controls the vertical spacing of a section.",
                {
                    "type": "section", 
                    "theme":"section--debug",
                    "data":
                    [
                        {
                            "type":"layout/one-col",
                            "data":[
                                {
                                    "type":"p",
                                    "data":"By default, sections have 1rem of top and bottom padding, which increases to 3rem above the medium breakpoint."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type":"raw",
                    "data":"<hr class='hr--bleed'/>"
                },
                {
                    "type":"raw",
                    "data":"<br />"
                },
                {
                    "type":"type/h4",
                    "data":"Layout"
                },
                "Three layout classes govern the horizontal width and spacing of content: ‘layout’, ‘layout--half’ and ‘layout--nudge’. ",
                {
                    "type":"raw",
                    "data":"<br />"
                },
                "1. <strong>layout</strong>",
                "This is the main layout class used throughout the site. It has a default left and right padding of 1rem, which changes to 4% above the medium breakpoint and again to 8.33% above the large breakpoint.",
                {
                    "type": "/pattern-library/layout"
                },
                {
                    "type":"raw",
                    "data":"<br /><br />"
                },
                "2.<strong>'Layout--half'</strong>",
                "This is mostly used to constrain the width of forms in the transactions section; ‘layout--half’ inherits the same behaviour as ‘layout’ and adjusts the left and right padding to 25% (instead of 8.33%) above the large breakpoint.",      
                {
                    "type": "pattern-library/layout--half"
                },

                {
                    "type":"raw",
                    "data":"<br /><br />"
                },
                "3.<strong>layout--nudge</strong>",
                "This modifier applies a negative margin of -2em to the top of an element. It doesn’t affect horizontal layout or spacing.",
                {
                    "type":"raw",
                    "data":"<hr class='hr--bleed'/>"
                },
                
                {
                    "type":"type/h4",
                    "data":"Container examples:"
                },
                "Here are some examples of containers we use throughout the site",
                {
